<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths end the same: a photo of a Chennai coastal location + 3 sentences identifying 2 active coastal processes. The path you pick is about how deep you go.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I can name longshore drift, wave erosion, and beach accretion, explain the role of monsoon storms in Chennai sediment cycling, and identify 2 active coastal processes at a coastal Chennai location of my choosing.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Pick a coastal Chennai location + identify 2 processes (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Choose any coastal Chennai stretch (Marina segments, Pulicat shore, Mahabalipuram, Kovalam, the port edge). Find a photo (Google Earth or curated). Identify 2 active coastal processes. 3 sentences total.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Compare your coast to Mahabalipuram</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Same starting move as Path A. Then add a 4th and 5th sentence comparing your coast to Mahabalipuram: what's similar in process, what's different in timescale, why. Strong prep for the Landscape Reading projections section.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Field Geologist consultation</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Open the <a href="/ai-partners/field-geologist/">Field Geologist</a>. Describe your chosen coast in detail (the partner can't see images — describe carefully). Ask it to help you reason about which processes are dominant and what evidence supports each. Document the exchange in your AI Doc.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-help — wave erosion vs. longshore drift</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Often confused. Come to the peer-help table if the distinction is fuzzy. Use the vocabulary handout + the longshore-drift animation from the Watch. Pair with a student who's solid. Mr. Ignash floats.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

